{
  "local_port": 58776,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I connect my PC's internet to my Windows Phone via USB or via Bluetooth?",
  "response": "To share your PC's internet connection with your Windows Phone, you have a couple of options: USB tethering and Bluetooth tethering. \n\n### USB Tethering\n\n1. **Enable Internet Connection Sharing on Your PC**:\n   - Open **Settings** on your PC.\n   - Click **Network & Internet**.\n   - Click **Mobile hotspot**.\n   - Turn on the **Share my Internet connection with other devices** toggle.\n   - Select **Wi-Fi** or **Ethernet** under the \"Share my Internet connection from\" dropdown.\n\n2. **Connect Your Windows Phone to Your PC**:\n   - Use a USB cable to connect your Windows Phone to your PC.\n\n3. **Enable USB Tethering on Your Windows Phone**:\n   - Unlock your Windows Phone and go to **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Network & Wireless**.\n   - Select **Mobile hotspot**.\n   - Enable **Share my cellular data connection over USB**.\n\nYour Windows Phone should now detect the shared internet connection from your PC via USB.\n\n### Bluetooth Tethering\n\n1. **Enable Internet Connection Sharing on Your PC**:\n   - Open **Settings** on your PC.\n   - Click **Network & Internet**.\n   - Click **Mobile hotspot**.\n   - Turn on the **Share my Internet connection with other devices** toggle.\n   - Select **Wi-Fi** or **Ethernet** under the \"Share my Internet connection from\" dropdown.\n\n2. **Pair Your Windows Phone and PC via Bluetooth**:\n   - On your PC, open **Settings**.\n   - Click **Devices**.\n   - Turn on **Bluetooth** and click on **Add Bluetooth or other device**.\n   - Select **Bluetooth** and follow the on-screen instructions to pair your Windows Phone with your PC.\n   \n   - On your Windows Phone, go to **Settings**.\n   - Tap **Devices** and enable **Bluetooth**.\n\n3. **Enable Bluetooth Tethering on Your Windows Phone**:\n   - After pairing, go to **Settings** on your Windows Phone.\n   - Navigate to **Network & Wireless**.\n   - Select **Mobile hotspot**.\n   - Enable **Share my cellular data connection over Bluetooth**.\n\nYour Windows Phone should be able to access the internet using your PC\u2019s connection shared via Bluetooth.\n\n### Troubleshooting Tips\n- Ensure both devices have Bluetooth turned on if using Bluetooth tethering.\n- Make sure your PC has active internet access.\n- Check if the drivers for your phone are updated on your PC.\n- Restart your devices if they do not connect properly.\n",
